.: Plot :.

July 2010: Beirut, Lebanon. Ten Italian volunteers take part in an international workcamp, which Arcs-Arci sets up in the Palestinian refugee camp of Bourj El-Barajneh. In order to promote encounter as a goal of the project, the coordinators decide to call the workcamp &quot;Nice Meeting You&quot; and ask Dot 2.0 to take care of the filming of the initiative.
This documentary aims at accounting for this experience..

